<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2373: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Military Attaché in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shipp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">War Department</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="94" xml:id="d369fn94">Received at the War Department
                                October 6, 1941, 6:48 p.m.; paraphrase received in Department of
                                State on October 8. Noted by the Secretary of State.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-06">October 6,
                                1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Within 6 months according to Japanese Military Attaché in Madrid the
                            United States and Japan would be at war.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shipp</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>